## Overview: How This Process Works

Most people try using ChatGPT to find their photos, but ChatGPT is hardcoded to block facial recognition. Instead, we use a specialized engine to locate the images, use ChatGPT to generate legal leverage, and then lock down your privacy.

1. **Harvest Your Links (The Audit):** Crucial: Do this before opting out.
Go to **PimEyes** and upload a clear selfie. The system will scan billions of public web pages, group shots, and background images.

**Action Item:** Do not just look at the results. Open every single match and copy the **exact URL** of the website hosting the image. Paste these into a notepad or document.


2. **Generate Takedown Letters via ChatGPT:** Forcing the source sites to delete the images.
PimEyes only indexes the web; it doesn't host your photos. To get them off the internet completely, you must contact the host websites. Copy the prompts provided in the section below, paste them into ChatGPT along with your links, and let it draft your legal letters.


3. **Submit the Takedown Requests:**
Find the "Contact Us," "Privacy," or "Support" email address for each website hosting your photo. Paste the text generated by ChatGPT, fill in the bracketed information, and send it.


4. **Execute the PimEyes Opt-Out:** Irreversible step.
Once you have successfully saved the links and sent your takedown notices, go to the PimEyes **PROtect / Opt-Out** page. Upload a photo and a heavily blurred copy of your government ID (mask out everything except your name and face for security). This permanently drops your face from their search index so no one else can look you up.


