## Copy-and-Paste ChatGPT Prompts

When contacting these websites, using standard legal language ensures your request is taken seriously. Use these exact prompts in ChatGPT depending on where you or the website are located.

### Option A: The GDPR Prompt (Best for Europe / UK or global privacy enforcement)

If you or the website operators are located in the EU or UK, or if the website operates globally, use this prompt to leverage strict privacy laws.

```text
Act as a digital privacy expert. Write a formal GDPR Article 17 "Right to Erasure" (Takedown) request directed to the website administrator. 

The website is currently hosting an unauthorized photograph containing my face at this URL: [INSERT YOUR PHOTO URL HERE]. 

The letter needs to formally state that I am withdrawing any implied consent for the processing and publication of my biometric data and personal image. Demand that they remove the image within the statutory 30 days and confirm deletion. Leave placeholders for my name and email address at the bottom.
```

### Option B: The DMCA Prompt (Best for US-based websites & copyright)

If the photo belongs to you (e.g., a selfie or a photo you took that someone else re-uploaded without permission), use this US copyright framework.

```text
Act as a intellectual property attorney. Draft a formal DMCA (Digital Millennium Copyright Act) Notice of Copyright Infringement. 

The infringing material is a photograph of me, which I own the copyright to, located at this exact URL: [INSERT YOUR PHOTO URL HERE]. 

The letter must include the standard legal elements: a statement made under penalty of perjury that I am the copyright owner, a statement that the use is unauthorized, and a demand for immediate removal. Leave brackets for my contact information and electronic signature.
```

